Jamie Pettingill was ordered to complete 350 hours of community service for stealing six mobile phones . 
  The 26-year-old robbed two women, a man and two schoolboys of their phones . 
  He threatened to slice off a schoolboy's face and sold the phones to fund a gambling addiction . 
  His father Trevor was acquitted of shooting two police constables in Melbourne's infamous 1988 Walsh Street murders . 
  Judge Sandra Davis said she feared his surname would bring him unwanted attention in prison . 
  He is the son of one of Australia's most notorious crime families . 
  The family inspired the film Animal Kingdom . 
 